#set working dir
setwd("~/Desktop/GutHeartProj/Metagenomics/2022_metagenomics/scripts_article/toGitHub/")

#Append time to output folders to avoid overlapping
st<-format(Sys.time(), '%d-%m-%Y')
fileunadj <- paste0("HF_234_maaslin_out_taxa_sp_unadjusted_", st)
fileadjust <- paste0("HF_234_maaslin_out_taxa_sp_adjusted_1", st)

Read data

# input data path
input_data<-("~/Desktop/GutHeartProj/Metagenomics/ABS/BL_merged_ABS_table_species.txt")

#input_metadata path
input_metadata<-("~/Desktop/GutHeartProj/GH_metadata_Finalver1_1_maaslin.tsv")

Run Maaslin2 - unadjusted

fit_data = Maaslin2(
  input_data = input_data, 
  input_metadata = input_metadata, 
  output = fileunadj, 
  max_significance = 0.05,
  fixed_effects = c("HFStatus"),
  reference= c('HFStatus,Control'),
  normalization = "TSS",
  correction = "BH",
  min_abundance = 1,
  min_prevalence = 0.1,
  transform = "LOG"
)

Maaslin run completed

Effect plot

if (nrow(sr1) > 2) {
  #print.data.frame(head(sr1))
  
  HFplot <- sr1 %>%
    dplyr::filter(qval < 0.05) %>% 
    dplyr::filter(value == "HeartFailure") %>% 
    mutate(high = ifelse(coef > 0, "high in HeartFailure", "low in HeartFailure"),
           feature = fct_reorder(feature, coef))
  
  efp<-ggplot(data = HFplot, aes(x = feature, y = coef, fill = high)) +
    geom_col(alpha = .8) +
    labs(y = "\nEffect size", x = "") + scale_x_discrete(label=function(x) abbreviate(x, minlength=100))+
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(color = "black", size = 8),
          axis.text.y = element_text(color = "black", size = 8),
          axis.title.y = element_text(size = 8),
          axis.title.x = element_text(size = 10),
          legend.text = element_text(size = 8),
          legend.title = element_text(size = 8)) +
    coord_flip() +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype="dotted") +
    scale_fill_manual("legend", values = c("high in HeartFailure" = "deeppink4", "low in HeartFailure" = "cyan4")) +
    theme(legend.position = "right")
  
  print(efp)
  
  ggsave("Maaslin2_EFplot_HFNORcohorts_.jpg",bg="white",width=10, height=6)
  
  
} else {
  print("## Not many significant fetaures \n ")
  
  print.data.frame(head(sr1))
}

forest plot

## Forest plot
if (nrow(sr1) > 2) {
  bf_df <- sr1 %>% 
    filter(value == "HeartFailure")
  
  (bf_res <- rma(yi = coef, sei = stderr, method = "REML", knha = TRUE, data = bf_df))
  
  forest(bf_res, addfit = TRUE, showweights = TRUE, header = TRUE, 
         slab = bf_df$feature,
         xlab = "Coef [95% CI]", mlab = "\nRandom Effects Model:\n")
} else {
  print("## Not many significant fetaures \n ")
  
  print.data.frame(head(sr1))
}

Run Maaslin2 - Adjusted for age sex bmi

fit_data = Maaslin2(
  input_data = input_data, 
  input_metadata = input_metadata, 
  output = fileadjust, 
  max_significance = 0.05,
  fixed_effects = c("HFStatus","Age", "Sex", "BMI"),
  reference= c('HFStatus,Control'),
  normalization = "TSS",
  correction = "BH",
  min_abundance = 1,
  min_prevalence = 0.1,
  transform = "LOG"
)
